## Third-party data sources

This project consumes character data from several upstream sources, each
with its own license. The MIT license above applies only to the
stroke-order Python code; data fetched / bundled at runtime retains its
original license. **When redistributing or deploying this project,
ensure compliance with the license of each data source you choose to
bundle.**

### A. Stroke / decomposition data

- **g0v/zh-stroke-data** — derived from MOE 教育部 standard kaishu data;
  see https://github.com/g0v/zh-stroke-data for licensing terms.
- **Make Me a Hanzi** — LGPL 3.0
  (https://github.com/skishore/makemeahanzi).
- **KanjiVG** — CC BY-SA 3.0 (https://github.com/KanjiVG/kanjivg).
- **CHISE / cjkvi-ids** — GPL-compatible IDS dataset
  (https://github.com/cjkvi/cjkvi-ids); consumed for component
  decomposition.

### B. Font assets (fetched at deploy time, not bundled in repo)

The Render.com deployment fetches these via
`scripts/render_fetch_fonts.sh` from GitHub Release `fonts-v1`. All
five sources permit redistribution under the terms below.

- **CNS 11643 全字庫 (TW-Kai-* / TW-Sung-* TTFs)** — Republic of China
  Ministry of Digital Affairs (數位發展部).
  License: 政府資料開放授權條款 1.0
  (Taiwan Open Government Data License 1.0).
  Source: https://www.cns11643.gov.tw/
  Permits free use, redistribution, and modification with attribution.

- **崇羲篆體 (chongxi_seal.otf)** — by 季旭昇 + Institute of Information
  Science, Academia Sinica.
  License: CC BY-ND 4.0 (Attribution-NoDerivatives).
  Source: https://github.com/ButTaiwan/chongxi
  Permits redistribution unmodified with attribution; **no derivative
  works**.

- **教育部標準楷書 (edukai.ttf)** — Republic of China Ministry of
  Education.
  License: 政府著作權聲明 / 政府資料開放授權 1.0.
  Source: https://language.moe.gov.tw/result.aspx?classify_sn=23
  Permits free use and redistribution with attribution.

- **教育部標準隸書 (MoeLI.ttf)** — Republic of China Ministry of
  Education.
  License: 政府著作權聲明 / 政府資料開放授權 1.0.
  Source: https://language.moe.gov.tw/result.aspx?classify_sn=23
  Permits free use and redistribution with attribution.

- **教育部標準宋體 (edusong_Unicode.ttf)** — Republic of China Ministry
  of Education.
  License: 政府著作權聲明 / 政府資料開放授權 1.0.
  Source: https://language.moe.gov.tw/result.aspx?classify_sn=23
  Permits free use and redistribution with attribution.

### C. Character cover-set datasets (built-in)

The five built-in cover-sets in `src/stroke_order/components/` are
derived from public-domain or government-published character lists:

- **cjk_common_808** — derived from the *中日韓共用漢字 808 字* booklet
  (TCS, 2014/2016) published by the Trilateral Cooperation Secretariat;
  https://www.tcs-asia.org/en/data/publications.php
  The character list itself is free-use as government-released data.

- **educational_4808** — derived from MOE 教育部 *常用國字標準字體表*
  (1982, 71 年公告). Public-domain government publication.
  Source: MOE official PDF + companion XLS.

- **moe_elementary_5021** — derived from MOE 教育部 *國民小學常用字彙*
  (2002, 91 年公告). Public-domain government publication.

- **bentu_6792** — derived from MOE 教育部 *本土語言成果參考字表*
  (2024, 113 年公告). Public-domain government publication.
  Includes Taiwan PUA / Ext G CNS-numbered characters.

- **wuqian_5000** — derived from 朱邦復 *漢字基因 5000 字單* (2012),
  publicly released character archive by Chu Bang-Fu.

### D. Attribution requirements when redistributing

If you build derivative works using stroke-order, in addition to
preserving the MIT notice above:

1. Preserve this entire `## Third-party data sources` section verbatim,
   or substitute equivalent attribution that names every source you
   actually bundle.
2. For **CC BY-ND** assets (崇羲篆體): redistribute only the unmodified
   font file; do not ship modified versions.
3. For **LGPL 3.0** code (Make Me a Hanzi consumers): comply with LGPL
   linkage requirements if you import their code directly.
4. For **CC BY-SA 3.0** assets (KanjiVG-derived data): downstream
   distribution of derivative datasets must use a CC BY-SA-compatible
   license.
